    "## 1. Problem Statement and Motivation\n",
    "\n",
    "### 1.1 Business Context\n",
    "\n",
    "Digital marketing teams allocate significant budgets across multiple channels like social media, email, PPC, SEO, and referral campaigns. However, a large portion of this spend targets users unlikely to convert, resulting in wasted resources, excessive ad exposure, and reduced return on investment. A predictive model that identifies which customers are likely to convert would enable smarter budget allocation and more responsible marketing practices.\n",
    "\n",
    "### 1.2 ML Problem Statement (Five-Part Structure)\n",
    "\n",
    "> **Predict whether** a *customer* (unit) **will convert** (event) **after interacting with a digital marketing campaign** (horizon), **using demographic, behavioral, and campaign data recorded during the campaign** (evidence/prediction time), **so that marketing managers can optimise ad spend, reduce wasted impressions, and focus resources on high-intent users** (action/impact).\n",
    "\n",
    "### 1.3 Classification Type\n",
    "\n",
    "This is a **binary classification** problem:\n",
    "- **Class 1 (Positive):** Customer converts  \n",
    "- **Class 0 (Negative):** Customer does not convert  \n",
    "\n",
    "### 1.4 Motivation and Real-World Impact\n",
    "\n",
    "This project connects to **SDG 12: Responsible Consumption and Production**. By predicting conversion likelihood, businesses can:\n",
    "- **Reduce wasted ad spend** on low-intent users  \n",
    "- **Decrease unnecessary digital exposure** (fewer irrelevant ads for customers)  \n",
    "- **Improve return on ad spend (ROAS)** by focusing on high-probability segments  \n",
    "\n",
    "**Target KPI:** Reduce cost per conversion by 15% while maintaining or improving total conversions over a 3–6 month period.\n",
    "\n",
    "### 1.5 Stakeholder Analysis\n",
    "\n",
    "| Stakeholder | Benefit / Risk |\n",
    "|---|---|\n",
    "| Marketing Managers | Direct benefit of better targeting, lower cost per conversion |\n",
    "| CRM Teams | Direct benefit of personalized outreach to high-intent users |\n",
    "| Customers | Indirect benefit of fewer irrelevant ads, better experience |\n",
    "| Business (Finance) | Indirect benefit of improved ROAS and budget efficiency |\n",
    "| Low-intent customers | Potential risk of receiving less engagement or being deprioritized |"
   ]
  },
