    "### 1.6 Success Metrics and Error-Cost Trade-offs\n",
    "\n",
    "**Primary Metric:** F1-Score (balances precision and recall for imbalanced data)  \n",
    "**Secondary Metrics:** ROC-AUC, Precision, Recall\n",
    "\n",
    "**Error-Cost Analysis:**\n",
    "\n",
    "| Error Type | Example | Business Cost |\n",
    "|---|---|---|\n",
    "| **False Positive** (predicted convert, didn't) | Budget allocated to a user who won't convert | Low–Medium — wasted ad spend |\n",
    "| **False Negative** (predicted no convert, did) | High-intent user ignored, missed conversion | Medium — lost revenue opportunity |\n",
    "\n",
    "Since neither error type is catastrophically more expensive than the other, **F1-Score** is the most appropriate primary metric. However, from a budget-efficiency perspective, **precision** is slightly prioritised — we want to avoid wasting spend on users who won't convert.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Baseline Target:** F1-Score > 0.60 on the minority class (non-conversion)  \n",
    "**Aspirational Target:** F1-Score > 0.75 with ROC-AUC > 0.85"
   ]
